verbose_text: 4 Studies on synoviocytes in vitro showed that Supartz FX suppressed the gene expression of several pro inflammatory cytokines (interleukin [IL]-1, IL-6, IL-8, tumor necrosis factor [TNF]-alpha), inducible nitric oxide synthase (iNOS), cyclooxygenase (COX)-2, collagenases (matrix metalloproteinase [MMP]-1, MMP-3), and aggrecanase (a disintegrin and metalloprotease with thrombospondin motifs [ADAMTS] 5).
